A thousand times I held them to my breast , A thousand times my lips the paper pressed : My full heart panted with a joy too strong , And " O , my prince ! " died faltering on my tongue : Fainting I sunk , unequal to the strife , And milder joys sustained returning life
Thy breast alone , when bounding over the waves To Freedom's climes , from slavery and slaves ; Thy breast alone the pleasing thought could frame Of what I felt , when thy dear letters

In vain I sought , some , conscious of my pain , With horrid silence
Some with a sneer the brutal thought expressed , And

whoever thou art , " Thy shrine the sky , the sea , the earth , or heart ; " Since every clime , and all the unbounded main , " And hostile barks , and storms , are thy domain , " If faithful passion can thy bounty move , " And goodness sure must be the friend of love , " Safe to these arms my lovely prince restore , " Safe to his Zara's arms , to part no more
OH ! grant to virtue thy protecting care , " And grant thy love to love's availing prayer
A flowery altar to thy name we'll raise
those hopes , and haste to me

writing prompts desire ; My pen denies my last farewell to write , Still , still , " return , " my wishful thoughts indite : OH ! hear , my prince , thy love , thy mistress call , Think over each tender name , and hear by all
